1.text: Let's study how singular nouns form their plurals.
1.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>Let's study how singular nouns form their plurals.</prosody></speak>

2.text: Most nouns form their plural form by adding -s to the singular form.
2.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>Most nouns form their plural form by adding -s to the singular form.</prosody></speak>

4.text: a dog dogs a boat boats a cat cats a song songs the shop the shops the tree the trees one teacher two teachers one book five books
4.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>a dog dogs a boat boats a cat cats a song songs the shop the shops the tree the trees one teacher two teachers one book five books</prosody></speak>

5.text: When a singular noun ends with s, sh, ch or x , its plural is formed by adding –es.
5.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>When a singular noun ends with s, sh, ch or x , its plural is formed by adding –es.</prosody></speak>

7.text: a bus buses a glass glasses a brush brushes a watch watches a box boxes
7.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>a bus buses a glass glasses a brush brushes a watch watches a box boxes</prosody></speak>

8.text: Some singular nouns ending with 'o' also takes –es when their plurals are formed.
8.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>Some singular nouns ending with 'o' also takes –es when their plurals are formed.</prosody></speak>
